The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 March is 40,611 (4,700.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 March, there were 336 new confirmed cases (38.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 623 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 46% (287 fewer cases).
